{{- /* device.json.tmpl — managed by chezmoi
   Stores the OpenClaw device keypair (ed25519). Preserving this across restores
   maintains continuity: paired devices (Clawket, web UI) keep working without re-pairing.

   Required Keychain entry (service=openclaw-identity):
     account=device_json_b64   full device.json content, base64-encoded

   Seed on a fresh system (run: openclaw-seed-keychain):
     security add-generic-password -U -s openclaw-identity -a device_json_b64 \
       -w "$(openssl base64 -A -in ~/.openclaw/identity/device.json)"
*/ -}}
{{ (output "sh" "-c" "security find-generic-password -s openclaw-identity -a device_json_b64 -w | openssl base64 -d") -}}
